The paper discusses the development of a Personal Health System (PHS) for monitoring patients with chronic diseases, specifically Type 1 Diabetes. The paper focuses on the use of knowledge engineering and temporal rules to handle the large amounts of data generated by patients. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of databases and indexing to efficiently handle the large amounts of data, which suggests that it may also belong to the Databases (cs.DB) sub-category. The paper also evaluates the efficiency of the proposed approach, which suggests that it may belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of graphical interfaces for representing monitoring rules, which suggests that it may belong to the Cybersecurity (cs.CYBER) sub-category. Finally, the paper focuses on the monitoring of patients with chronic diseases, which suggests that it may also belong to the Human-Computer Interaction (cs.HC) sub-category.
